<TITLE> Coastguards foil fertiliser smuggling </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  Coastguards Friday arrested a member of a fertiliser smuggling syndicate from a shop in Dohazari under Chandanaish upazila in the district. The coastguards also seized 1,200 bags of urea fertiliser from the spot which were waiting to be smuggled out to Myanmar. Lieutenant commander Ehsan Ullah of the coastguards told bdnews24.com that they have mounted watch along the coasts and into the deeper regions of the Bay to check fertiliser smuggling. Tipped off, the coastguards and the local administration jointly raided Motaleb Store in Dohazari market early hours Friday and unearthed 1,200 bags of urea fertiliser. The arrested Dulal Das is associated with coastal manure smuggling gangs, Ehsan said. Dulal was handed over to Chandanaish police, he said. bdnews24.
